hpnicfEOCCommon.name: hpnicfEOCCommon
hpnicfEOCCommon.description: The objects in this MIB module are used to manage and display common configuration between Ethernet Passive Optical Network (EOC) port which are based on the Ethernet in the First Mile (EFM) Passive Optical Network(PON) as defined in IEEE Draft P802.3ah/D3.0 clause 60, 64, 65.. and Ethernet Over Cable (EOC) which is based on HomePlug AV Specification.

hpnicfEOCCommonSysVersion.name: hpnicfEOCCommonSysVersion
hpnicfEOCCommonSysVersion.description: Eoc version. If the object length is zero, it means the version is unknown. The length is up to 1024.

hpnicfEOCCommonUpLinkMacAddress.name: hpnicfEOCCommonUpLinkMacAddress
hpnicfEOCCommonUpLinkMacAddress.description: EOC CLT's uplink device's mac address.

hpnicfEOCCommonCltManTable.name: hpnicfEOCCommonCltManTable
hpnicfEOCCommonCltManTable.description: This table defines the primary parameters of the CLT configuration.

hpnicfEOCCommonCltManEntry.name: hpnicfEOCCommonCltManEntry
hpnicfEOCCommonCltManEntry.description: The entry of the table hpnicfEOCCommonCltManTable.

hpnicfEOCCommonCltAutoAuthorize.name: hpnicfEOCCommonCltAutoAuthorize
hpnicfEOCCommonCltAutoAuthorize.description: This value determines whether software performs self-authorization for each Cable Network Unit(CNU) registering to the network. Setting it to false means for every CNU registering, software requires external authorization, and until it's done the CNU is not authenticated. True value means software authorizes each CNU registering to the network automatically.

hpnicfEOCCommonCltMaxAllowToAccess.name: hpnicfEOCCommonCltMaxAllowToAccess
hpnicfEOCCommonCltMaxAllowToAccess.description: This value determines how many CNU can be bound in this CLT. If the number of CNU is more than this value , then the rest of CNU should not be allow to access.

hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxDownBWMinVal.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxDownBWMinVal
hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxDownBWMinVal.description: The lower limit of total-bandwidth which is confined to hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxDownBW.

hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxDownBWMaxVal.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxDownBWMaxVal
hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxDownBWMaxVal.description: The upper limit of total-bandwidth which is confined to hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxDownBW.

hpnicfEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBWMinVal.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBWMinVal
hpnicfEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBWMinVal.description: The lower limit of high priority bandwidth which is confined to hpnicfEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBW.

hpnicfEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBWMaxVal.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBWMaxVal
hpnicfEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBWMaxVal.description: The upper limit of high priority bandwidth which is confined to hpnicfEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBW.

hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxUpBWMinVal.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxUpBWMinVal
hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxUpBWMinVal.description: The lower limit of total-bandwidth which is confined to hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxUpBW.

hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxUpBWMaxVal.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxUpBWMaxVal
hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxUpBWMaxVal.description: The upper limit of total-bandwidth which is confined to hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxUpBW.

hpnicfEOCComCnuAttenThrA.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuAttenThrA
hpnicfEOCComCnuAttenThrA.description: The value of cnu's average attenuation good level thresholds.

hpnicfEOCComCnuAttenThrB.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuAttenThrB
hpnicfEOCComCnuAttenThrB.description: The value of cnu's average attenuation normal level thresholds.

hpnicfEOCComCnuRateDropThr.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuRateDropThr
hpnicfEOCComCnuRateDropThr.description: The value of cnu's Tx/Rx rate drop thresholds.

hpnicfEOCComCnuSysManTable.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuSysManTable
hpnicfEOCComCnuSysManTable.description: This table implements the management of CNUs(Coax Network Unit).

hpnicfEOCComCnuSysManEntry.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuSysManEntry
hpnicfEOCComCnuSysManEntry.description: The entry of the table hpnicfEOCComCnuSysManTable.

hpnicfEOCComCnuCableIfindex.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuCableIfindex
hpnicfEOCComCnuCableIfindex.description: The index of cable port which uniquely identifies the cable port of one device.

hpnicfEOCComCnuDeviceType.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuDeviceType
hpnicfEOCComCnuDeviceType.description: The type of the EOC CNU(Coax Network Unit).

hpnicfEOCComCnuDeviceAlias.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuDeviceAlias
hpnicfEOCComCnuDeviceAlias.description: EOC CNU's alias which display as the device's name, it's recommended to set it uniquely and understandably.

hpnicfEOCComCnuDescr.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuDescr
hpnicfEOCComCnuDescr.description: User's description, including user's address, name, telephone number and so on.

hpnicfEOCComCnuUpTime.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuUpTime
hpnicfEOCComCnuUpTime.description: The time since the CNU last registered to the network.

hpnicfEOCComCnuVLANType.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuVLANType
hpnicfEOCComCnuVLANType.description: port vlan types. hybrid (3) port can carry multiple VLANs. If fabric function is supported, fabric(4) means the port is a fabric port.

hpnicfEOCComCnuPvid.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuPvid
hpnicfEOCComCnuPvid.description: The PVID, the VLAN ID assigned to untagged frames or Priority-Tagged frames received on cable interface.

hpnicfEOCComCnuVlanTag.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuVlanTag
hpnicfEOCComCnuVlanTag.description: VLAN is set tagged or untagged on cable interface.

hpnicfEOCComCnuReset.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuReset
hpnicfEOCComCnuReset.description: This variable is used to reset the CNU device. The interface may be unavailable while the reset occurs and data may be lost. During reading operation it returns the state of the CNU device. running(1) indicates and operates normal operation, reset(2) indicates and operates reset mode. Writing can be done all the time.

hpnicfEOCComCnuSave.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuSave
hpnicfEOCComCnuSave.description: Save the UNI and CNU related configurations to the CNU.

hpnicfEOCComCnuAccess.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuAccess
hpnicfEOCComCnuAccess.description: Control whether the user can access to the network.

hpnicfEOCComCnuMacTable.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuMacTable
hpnicfEOCComCnuMacTable.description: This table implements the management of CNUs.

hpnicfEOCComCnuMacEntry.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuMacEntry
hpnicfEOCComCnuMacEntry.description: The entry of the table hpnicfEOCComCnuMacTable.

hpnicfEOCComCnuTempIndex.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuTempIndex
hpnicfEOCComCnuTempIndex.description: EOC CNU's model index from hpnicfHPEOCTemplateIndex, If configure 0, the CNU select no model.

hpnicfEOCComCnuInfoTable.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuInfoTable
hpnicfEOCComCnuInfoTable.description: Primary status of the specified CNU. There will be one row in this table for each information in the system.

hpnicfEOCComCnuHardwareVersion.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuHardwareVersion
hpnicfEOCComCnuHardwareVersion.description: EOC CNU's hardware version. If the object length is zero, it means the version is unknown.

hpnicfEOCComCnuLinkState.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuLinkState
hpnicfEOCComCnuLinkState.description: The cable port's link state. The physicaldown(1) state indicates that the CNU is not powered on. The linkdown(2) state indicates that the CNU is powered on, but registers fail. The linkup(3) state indicates that the CNU is powered on, and registers successful. The loopback(4) state indecates that the CNU is powered on and registers successful, but loopback has detected.

hpnicfEOCComCnuSoftwareVersion.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuSoftwareVersion
hpnicfEOCComCnuSoftwareVersion.description: EOC CNU's software version. If the object length is zero, it means the version is unknown.

hpnicfEOCComCnuTxRate.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuTxRate
hpnicfEOCComCnuTxRate.description: The cnu's capability of tx speed in unit of 1Mbps.

hpnicfEOCComCnuRxRate.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuRxRate
hpnicfEOCComCnuRxRate.description: The cnu's capability of rx speed in unit of 1Mbps.

hpnicfEOCComCnuTxRateDrop.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuTxRateDrop
hpnicfEOCComCnuTxRateDrop.description: The cnu's capability droping of tx speed from it's history max value in unit of %.

hpnicfEOCComCnuRxRateDrop.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuRxRateDrop
hpnicfEOCComCnuRxRateDrop.description: The cnu's capability droping of rx speed from it's history max value in unit of %.

hpnicfEOCComCnuBandWidthEntry.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuBandWidthEntry
hpnicfEOCComCnuBandWidthEntry.description: The entry of table hpnicfEOCComCnuBandWidthTable. It is a pre-configuration.

hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxDownBW.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxDownBW
hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxDownBW.description: Maximum bandwidth allowed for the CNU, measured in Kbit/s.

hpnicfEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBW.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBW
hpnicfEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBW.description: High priority bandwidth - measured in Kbit/s. The value of this object should be the multiple of the value of hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxUpBW. The high priority bandwidth should not be larger than the maximum bandwidth.

hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxUpBW.name: hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxUpBW
hpnicfEOCComCnuMaxUpBW.description: Total bandwidth - measured in Kbit/s. The value of this object should be the multiple of the value of hpnicfEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBW. The total bandwidth should be larger than the high priority bandwidth.

hpnicfEOCComUniManTable.name: hpnicfEOCComUniManTable
hpnicfEOCComUniManTable.description: This table defines several user network interface(UNI) system parameters.

hpnicfEOCUniIndex.name: hpnicfEOCUniIndex
hpnicfEOCUniIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the FE(Fast Ethernet) interface of the CNU.

hpnicfEOCComUniDescr.name: hpnicfEOCComUniDescr
hpnicfEOCComUniDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the interface. This string should include the name of the manufacturer, the product name and the version of the interface hardware and software.

hpnicfEOCComUniStatus.name: hpnicfEOCComUniStatus
hpnicfEOCComUniStatus.description: The desired state of the user network interface. When a managed system initializes, all user network interfaces start with down state. The testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed. As a result of either explicit management action or per configuration information retained by the managed system, hpnicfEOCComUniStatus is then changed to either the up or testing states (or remains in the down state).

hpnicfEOCComUniCurrentSpeed.name: hpnicfEOCComUniCurrentSpeed
hpnicfEOCComUniCurrentSpeed.description: An estimate of the interface's current bandwidth in bits per second. For interfaces which do not vary in bandwidth or for those where no accurate estimation can be made, this object should contain the nominal bandwidth. If the bandwidth of the interface is greater than the maximum value reportable by this object then this object should report its maximum value (4,294,967,295). For a sub-layer which has no concept of bandwidth, this object should be zero.

hpnicfEOCComUniCurrentDuplex.name: hpnicfEOCComUniCurrentDuplex
hpnicfEOCComUniCurrentDuplex.description: The current mode of operation of the MAC entity. 'unknown' indicates that the current duplex mode could not be determined. Management control of the duplex mode is accomplished through the MAU MIB. When an interface does not support autonegotiation, or when autonegotiation is not enabled, the duplex mode is controlled using ifMauDefaultType. When autonegotiation is supported and enabled, duplex mode is controlled using ifMauAutoNegAdvertisedBits. In either case, the currently operating duplex mode is reflected both in this object and in ifMauType. Note that this object provides redundant information with ifMauType. Normally, redundant objects are discouraged. However, in this instance, it allows a management application to determine the duplex status of an interface without having to know every possible value of ifMauType. This was felt to be sufficiently valuable to justify the redundancy.

hpnicfEOCComUniMdi.name: hpnicfEOCComUniMdi
hpnicfEOCComUniMdi.description: Type of the line connected to UNI interface: mdi-ii(straight-through cable), mdi-x (crossover cable), mdi-auto (auto-sensing).

hpnicfEOCComUniFlowControl.name: hpnicfEOCComUniFlowControl
hpnicfEOCComUniFlowControl.description: Flow control status. true(1) - Flow control status enable. false(2) - Flow control status disable.

hpnicfEOCComUniCountReset.name: hpnicfEOCComUniCountReset
hpnicfEOCComUniCountReset.description: Reset the counter which is about packets of the interface, then the counter will change to zero. There is no sense in reading this object.

hpnicfEOCComUniAlias.name: hpnicfEOCComUniAlias
hpnicfEOCComUniAlias.description: This object is an 'alias' name for the interface as specified by a network manager, and provides a non- volatile 'handle' for the interface. On the first instantiation of an interface, the value of hpnicfEOCComUniAlias associated with that interface is the zero-length string. As and when a value is written into an instance of hpnicfEOCComUniAlias through a network management set operation, then the agent must retain the supplied value in the hpnicfEOCComUniAlias instance associated with the same interface for as long as that interface remains instantiated, including across all re- initializations/reboots of the network management system, including those which result in a change of the interface's ifIndex and hpnicfEOCUniIndex value. An example of the value which a network manager might store in this object for a WAN interface is the (Telco's) circuit number/identifier of the interface. Some agents may support write-access only for interfaces having particular values of hpnicfEOCComUniType. An agent which supports write access to this object is required to keep the value in non-volatile storage, but it may limit the length of new values depending on how much storage is already occupied by the current values for other interfaces.

hpnicfEOCComUniType.name: hpnicfEOCComUniType
hpnicfEOCComUniType.description: The type of interface. Additional values for hpnicfEOCComUniType are assigned by the Internet Assigned Numbers Authority(IANA), through updating the syntax of the IANAifType textual convention.

hpnicfEOCComUniVLANType.name: hpnicfEOCComUniVLANType
hpnicfEOCComUniVLANType.description: port vlan types. hybrid (3) port can carry multiple VLANs. If fabric function is supported, fabric(4) means the port is a fabric port.

hpnicfEOCComUniPvid.name: hpnicfEOCComUniPvid
hpnicfEOCComUniPvid.description: The PVID, the VLAN ID assigned to untagged frames or Priority-Tagged frames received on this port.

hpnicfEOCComUniVlanTag.name: hpnicfEOCComUniVlanTag
hpnicfEOCComUniVlanTag.description: VLAN is set tagged or untagged.

hpnicfEOCComUniPriority.name: hpnicfEOCComUniPriority
hpnicfEOCComUniPriority.description: The default ingress User Priority for this port. This only has effect on media, such as Ethernet, that do not support native User Priority.

hpnicfEOCComUniUpLineRate.name: hpnicfEOCComUniUpLineRate
hpnicfEOCComUniUpLineRate.description: The max speed upload in units of 1,000 bits per second on this interface. The value should between 0 and 100Mbps. If the value is 0, it means that the upload speed is only restricted by the physical line.

hpnicfEOCComUniDownLineRate.name: hpnicfEOCComUniDownLineRate
hpnicfEOCComUniDownLineRate.description: The max speed download in units of 1,000 bits per second on this interface. The value should between 0 and 100Mbps. If the value is 0, it means that the download speed is only restricted by the physical line.

hpnicfEOCComUniAdminStatus.name: hpnicfEOCComUniAdminStatus
hpnicfEOCComUniAdminStatus.description: Control if open or close the UNI. If choose up(1), means the UNI is opened and packets can pass it. If choose down(2), means the UNI is closed and all packets will be discard.

hpnicfEOCComUniCountTable.name: hpnicfEOCComUniCountTable
hpnicfEOCComUniCountTable.description: A list of interface counter about frames entries.

hpnicfEOCComUniCountEntry.name: hpnicfEOCComUniCountEntry
hpnicfEOCComUniCountEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular interface.

hpnicfEOCUniInPkts.name: hpnicfEOCUniInPkts
hpnicfEOCUniInPkts.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets, broadcast packets, and multicast packets) received.

hpnicfEOCUniInUPkts.name: hpnicfEOCUniInUPkts
hpnicfEOCUniInUPkts.description: The total number of good packets received that are directed to the unicast address. Note that this does not include multicast and broadcast packets.

hpnicfEOCUniInBPkts.name: hpnicfEOCUniInBPkts
hpnicfEOCUniInBPkts.description: The total number of good packets received that are directed to the broadcast address. Note that this does not include multicast packets.

hpnicfEOCUniInMPkts.name: hpnicfEOCUniInMPkts
hpnicfEOCUniInMPkts.description: The total number of good packets received that are directed to a multicast address. Note that this number does not include packets directed to the broadcast address.

hpnicfEOCUniInPausePkts.name: hpnicfEOCUniInPausePkts
hpnicfEOCUniInPausePkts.description: A count of MAC Control packets received on this interface by the pause(flow control) operation. This counter does not increment when the interface is in a half-duplex mode. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system.

hpnicfEOCUniInTotalErrors.name: hpnicfEOCUniInTotalErrors
hpnicfEOCUniInTotalErrors.description: Total count of the error packets received on this interface.

hpnicfEOCUniInCRCErrs.name: hpnicfEOCUniInCRCErrs
hpnicfEOCUniInCRCErrs.description: The total number of packets received that had a length (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) of between 64 and 1518 octets, inclusive, but had either a bad Frame Check Sequence (FCS) with an integral number of octets (FCS Error) or a bad FCS with a non-integral number of octets (Alignment Error).

hpnicfEOCUniInUndersizePkts.name: hpnicfEOCUniInUndersizePkts
hpnicfEOCUniInUndersizePkts.description: The total number of packets received that are less than 64 octets long (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and are otherwise well formed.

hpnicfEOCUniInOversizePkts.name: hpnicfEOCUniInOversizePkts
hpnicfEOCUniInOversizePkts.description: The total number of packets received that are longer than 1518 octets (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and are otherwise well formed.

hpnicfEOCUniInErrorbyOther.name: hpnicfEOCUniInErrorbyOther
hpnicfEOCUniInErrorbyOther.description: The total number of other error packets received on this interface.

hpnicfEOCUniInOctets.name: hpnicfEOCUniInOctets
hpnicfEOCUniInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on this interface.

hpnicfEOCUniOutPkts.name: hpnicfEOCUniOutPkts
hpnicfEOCUniOutPkts.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets, broadcast packets, and multicast packets) sent.

hpnicfEOCUniOutUPkts.name: hpnicfEOCUniOutUPkts
hpnicfEOCUniOutUPkts.description: The total number of good packets sent that are directed to the unicast address. Note that this does not include multicast and broadcast packets.

hpnicfEOCUniOutBPkts.name: hpnicfEOCUniOutBPkts
hpnicfEOCUniOutBPkts.description: The total number of good packets sent that are directed to the broadcast address. Note that this does not include multicast packets.

hpnicfEOCUniOutMPkts.name: hpnicfEOCUniOutMPkts
hpnicfEOCUniOutMPkts.description: The total number of good packets sent that are directed to a multicast address. Note that this number does not include packets directed to the broadcast address.

hpnicfEOCUniOutPausePkts.name: hpnicfEOCUniOutPausePkts
hpnicfEOCUniOutPausePkts.description: The total number of MAC control packets sent on this interface by the pause operation. This counter does not increment when the interface is in a half-duplex mode. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system.

hpnicfEOCUniOutTotalErrors.name: hpnicfEOCUniOutTotalErrors
hpnicfEOCUniOutTotalErrors.description: The total number of error packets sent on this interface.

hpnicfEOCUniOutCollisions.name: hpnicfEOCUniOutCollisions
hpnicfEOCUniOutCollisions.description: The best estimate of the total number of collisions on this Ethernet segment. The value returned will depend on the location of the RMON probe. Section 8.2.1.3 (10BASE-5) and section 10.3.1.3 (10BASE-2) of IEEE standard 802.3 states that a station must detect a collision, in the receive mode, if three or more stations are transmitting simultaneously. A repeater port must detect a collision when two or more stations are transmitting simultaneously. Thus a probe placed on a repeater port could record more collisions than a probe connected to a station on the same segment could. Probe location plays a much smaller role when considering 10BASE-T. 14.2.1.4 (10BASE-T) of IEEE standard 802.3 defines a collision as the simultaneous presence of signals on the DO and RD circuits (transmitting and receiving at the same time). A 10BASE-T station can only detect collisions when it is transmitting. Thus probes placed on a station and a repeater, should report the same number of collisions. Note also that an RMON probe inside a repeater should ideally report collisions between the repeater and one or more other hosts (transmit collisions as defined by IEEE 802.3k) plus receiver collisions observed on any coax segments to which the repeater is connected.

hpnicfEOCUniOutDelayExceedDsds.name: hpnicfEOCUniOutDelayExceedDsds
hpnicfEOCUniOutDelayExceedDsds.description: The number of packets discarded by this port due to excessive transit delay through the bridge. It is incremented by both transparent and source route bridges.

hpnicfEOCUniOutErrorbyOther.name: hpnicfEOCUniOutErrorbyOther
hpnicfEOCUniOutErrorbyOther.description: The total number of other error packets sent on this interface. Other error packets means the error packets out of collision packets and excessive delayed packets.

hpnicfEOCUniOutDroppedFrames.name: hpnicfEOCUniOutDroppedFrames
hpnicfEOCUniOutDroppedFrames.description: The total number of frames dropped because of buffer failure.

hpnicfEOCUniOutOctets.name: hpnicfEOCUniOutOctets
hpnicfEOCUniOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the interface.

hpnicfEOCCnuRegExcessTrap.name: hpnicfEOCCnuRegExcessTrap
hpnicfEOCCnuRegExcessTrap.description: A hpnicfEOCCnuRegExcessTrap notification is sent when the number of registered CNUs exceeds the limit.

hpnicfEOCCnuRegExcessRecoverTrap.name: hpnicfEOCCnuRegExcessRecoverTrap
hpnicfEOCCnuRegExcessRecoverTrap.description: A hpnicfEOCCnuRegExcessRecoverTrap notification is sent when hpnicfEOCCnuRegExcessTrap is detected and then recoverd.

hpnicfEOCCnuRegSuccTrap.name: hpnicfEOCCnuRegSuccTrap
hpnicfEOCCnuRegSuccTrap.description: A hpnicfEOCCnuRegSuccTrap notification is sent when a CNU registers successful.

hpnicfEOCCnuOffLineTrap.name: hpnicfEOCCnuOffLineTrap
hpnicfEOCCnuOffLineTrap.description: A hpnicfEOCCnuOffLineTrap notification is sent when a CNU offline.

hpnicfEOCCnuLinkupTrap.name: hpnicfEOCCnuLinkupTrap
hpnicfEOCCnuLinkupTrap.description: A hpnicfEOCCnuLinkupTrap notification is sent when a CNU linkup.

hpnicfEOCOamDisconnectTrap.name: hpnicfEOCOamDisconnectTrap
hpnicfEOCOamDisconnectTrap.description: A hpnicfEOCOamDisconnectionTrap notification is sent when LLID's OAM link is disconnected.

hpnicfEOCOamDisconnectRecoverTrap.name: hpnicfEOCOamDisconnectRecoverTrap
hpnicfEOCOamDisconnectRecoverTrap.description: A hpnicfEOCOamDisconnectionRecoverTrap notification is sent when LLID's OAM link is disconnected and then connected.

hpnicfEOCBandwidthNotEnoughTrap.name: hpnicfEOCBandwidthNotEnoughTrap
hpnicfEOCBandwidthNotEnoughTrap.description: Bandwidth is not enough, cnu can not bind now.

hpnicfEOCCnuAttenuationTrap.name: hpnicfEOCCnuAttenuationTrap
hpnicfEOCCnuAttenuationTrap.description: A hpnicfHPEOCCnuAttenuationTrap notification is sent when a CNU's attenuation is changing.

hpnicfEOCCnuRegFailTrap.name: hpnicfEOCCnuRegFailTrap
hpnicfEOCCnuRegFailTrap.description: A hpnicfEOCCnuRegFailTrap notification is sent when a CNU registers fail.

hpnicfEOCCLTCablePortErrorTrap.name: hpnicfEOCCLTCablePortErrorTrap
hpnicfEOCCLTCablePortErrorTrap.description: A hpnicfEOCCLTCablePortErrorTrap notification is sent when the hardware of cable port occurs error or CLT's vlan is configged error.

hpnicfEOCCLTCablePortErrReTrap.name: hpnicfEOCCLTCablePortErrReTrap
hpnicfEOCCLTCablePortErrReTrap.description: A hpnicfEOCCLTCablePortErrReTrap notification is sent when cable port error and then recovered.

hpnicfEOCCnuTxRateDropTrap.name: hpnicfEOCCnuTxRateDropTrap
hpnicfEOCCnuTxRateDropTrap.description: A hpnicfEOCCnuTxRateDropTrap notification is sent when cable port rate of TX capability drop exceeded threshold.

hpnicfEOCCnuTxRateDropRecoverTrap.name: hpnicfEOCCnuTxRateDropRecoverTrap
hpnicfEOCCnuTxRateDropRecoverTrap.description: A hpnicfEOCCnuTxRateDropRecoverTrap notification is sent when cable port rate of TX capability recover from the recent rate-drop trap.

hpnicfEOCCnuRxRateDropTrap.name: hpnicfEOCCnuRxRateDropTrap
hpnicfEOCCnuRxRateDropTrap.description: A hpnicfEOCCnuRxRateDropTrap notification is sent when cable port rate of RX capability drop exceeded threshold.

hpnicfEOCCnuRxRateDropRecoverTrap.name: hpnicfEOCCnuRxRateDropRecoverTrap
hpnicfEOCCnuRxRateDropRecoverTrap.description: A hpnicfEOCCnuRxRateDropRecoverTrap notification is sent when cable port rate of RX capability recover from the recent rate-drop trap.

hpnicfEOCCnuFWDownLoadErrTrap.name: hpnicfEOCCnuFWDownLoadErrTrap
